4hk.title: Sign homomorphism (from the symmetric group)
4hk.clickbait: The sign homomorphism is how we extract the alternating group from the symmetric group.
4hk.text:
The sign [47t homomorphism] is given by sending a permutation $\sigma$ in the [-497] $S_n$ to $0$ if we can make $\sigma$ by multiplying together an even number of [4cn transpositions], and to $1$ otherwise.

%%%knows-requisite([modular_arithmetic]):
Equivalently, it is given by sending $\sigma$ to the number of transpositions making it up, [modular_arithmetic modulo] $2$.
%%%

The sign homomorphism [4hh is well-defined].

%%%knows-requisite([quotient_group]):
The [-alternating_group] is obtained by taking the [quotient_group quotient] of the symmetric group by the sign homomorphism.
%%%
